The equipartition theorem says that the average of any quadratic degree of freedom is \(\frac{1}{2}
k_BT\). In short, the reason why each mode contributes \(k_BT\) is because harmonic oscillators have two quadratic degrees of freedom — one in position, the other in momentum. Each contributes \(\frac{1}{2}
k_BT\), so in total each mode contributes \(k_BT\). For a more detailed explanation, consult a statistical mechanics book.↩︎
